 mathematicians and theoretical physicists held in Strasbourg in May 2001. Topics covered are: star-products over Poisson manifolds, quantization of Hopf algebras, index theorems, globalization and cohomological problems. Both the mathematical and the physical approach ranging from asymptotic quantum electrodynamics to operads and prop theory will be presented. Historical remarks and surveys set the results presented in perspective. Directed at research mathematicians and theoretical physicists as well as graduate students, the volume will give an overview of a field of research that has seen enourmous acticity in the last years, with new ties to many other areas of mathematics and physics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aGeometric quantizationvCongresses. 0aMathematical physicsvCongresses. 4aDeformationsquantisierung. 4aKongress. 4aStraßburg ‹2001›. 7aMATHEMATICS / General.2bisacsh1 aArnaudon, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAvan, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCattaneo, Alberto S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDito, Giuseppe, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFedosov, Boris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFelder, Giovanni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrappat, Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrønsdal, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalbout, Gilles, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalbout, Gilles, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMonvel, Louis Boutet de, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vo